Here's my issue with this PR: the use case is extremely narrow (one specific plugin calling one specific API function, and even only in very special circumstances). This does not justify adding a new option which _affects global state_ -- even if the value is local to a buffer, it will affect _all_ plugins acting on that buffer, and one may want to raise the limit while another wants to lower it. (Didn't you watch @famiu's talk? Options are a mistake.)

So I don't think this approach is acceptable. A compromise could be to add `match_limit` as an optional argument to `iter_captures` and/or `iter_matches`, and leave the logic whether and how to adjust it to calling plugins.

@lewis6991
